#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:154
msgid "Custom Curve"
msgstr "自定义曲线"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:156
msgid "The *Custom Curve* lamp *Falloff* type is very flexible."
msgstr "*自定义曲线（Custom Curve)* 灯光 *衰减(Falloff)* 类型非常灵活。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:158
msgid ""
"Most other lamp falloff types work by having their light intensity start at its "
"maximum (when nearest to the light source) and then with some predetermined "
"pattern decrease their light intensity when the distance from the light source "
"increases."
msgstr ""
"大多数其他的灯光衰减类型的工作原理是使它们的光强度从最大值开始（当最接近光源"
"时），然后在某种预定的模式下，当随着光源的距离增加时，降低它们的光强度。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:162
msgid ""
"When using the *Custom Curve* Lamp Falloff type, a new panel is created, called "
"*Falloff Curve*. This *Falloff Curve* profile graph allows the user to alter "
"how intense light is at a particular point along a light's attenuation profile "
"(i.e. at a specific distance from the light source)."
msgstr ""
"当使用 *自定义曲线* 灯光衰减类型时，将创建一个新面板，称为 *衰减曲线（Falloff "
"Curve）* 。此 *衰减曲线（Falloff Curve）* 轮廓图允许用户更改灯光衰减轮廓（即在距"
"光源特定距离处）上特定点处的强度。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:167
msgid ""
"The *Falloff Curve* profile graph has two axes, the Distance axis and the "
"Intensity axis."
msgstr "*衰减曲线* 轮廓图有两个轴，距离轴和强度轴。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:172
msgid "Distance axis"
msgstr "距离轴"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:171
msgid ""
"It represents the position at a particular point along a light source's "
"attenuation path. The far left is at the position of the light source and the "
"far right is the place where the light source's influence would normally be "
"completely attenuated."
msgstr ""
"它表示光源衰减路径上特定点的位置。最左边是光源的位置，最右边是光源的影响通常会是"
"完全减弱的地方。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:177
msgid "Intensity axis"
msgstr "强度轴"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:175
msgid ""
"It represents the intensity at a particular point along a light source's "
"attenuation path. Higher intensity is represented by being higher up the "
"intensity axis, while lower intensity light is represented by being lower down "
"on the intensity axis."
msgstr ""
"它表示沿光源衰减路径的特定点的强度。通过在强度轴上向上表示较高强度，而在强度轴上"
"向下表示较低强度的光。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:179
msgid ""
"Altering the *Falloff Curve* profile graph is easy. Just :kbd:`LMB` click on a "
"part of the graph you want to alter and drag it where you want it to be. If "
"when you click you are over or near one of the tiny black square handles, it "
"will turn white, indicating that this handle is now selected, and you will be "
"able to drag it to a new position. If when you click on the graph you are not "
"near a handle, one will be created at the point that you clicked, which you can "
"then drag where you wish. You can also create handles at specific parts of the "
"graph, clicking with :kbd:`LMB` while holding :kbd:`Ctrl`; it will create a new "
"handle at the point you have clicked."
msgstr ""
"改变 *衰减曲线* 轮廓图很容易。只需 :kbd:`LMB` 单击要更改的图形的一部分并将其拖动"
"到您想要的位置。如果单击某个小的黑色方形手柄或其附近，则该手柄将变为白色，表示该"
"手柄已被选中，你可以将其拖动到新位置。如果单击图形时没有靠近手柄，则会在你单击的"
"位置创建一个，然后可以将其拖动到所需位置。你也可以在图形的特定部分创建手柄，点"
"击 :kbd:`LMB` ，同时按住 :kbd:`Ctrl` 它将在你单击的位置创建一个新手柄。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:190
msgid ""
"In the example below (the default for the *Falloff Curve* Profile Graph), the "
"graph shows that the intensity of the light starts off at its maximum (when "
"near the light), and linearly attenuates as it moves to the right (further away "
"from the light source)."
msgstr ""
"在下面的示例中（ *衰减曲线* 轮廓图的默认值），图表显示光的强度从最大值开始（靠近"
"灯光时），并在向右移动时线性衰减（远离光源）。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:200
msgid "Default Falloff Curve panel graph."
msgstr "默认衰减曲线面板图。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:205
msgid ""
"Render showing the Custom Curve lamp falloff type effect with default settings."
msgstr "使用默认设置渲染显示自定义曲线灯衰减类型效果。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:207
msgid ""
"If you want to have a light attenuation profile that gets more intense as it "
"moves away from the light source, you could alter the graph as below:"
msgstr ""
"如果你希望灯光衰减曲线在远离光源时变得更加强烈，您可以更改图形，如下所示："

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:215
msgid "Falloff Curve for reversed attenuation."
msgstr "反向衰减的衰减曲线。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:220
msgid "Falloff Curve for reversed attenuation rendered."
msgstr "反向衰减渲染的衰减曲线。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:222
msgid ""
"You are obviously not just limited to simple changes such as reversing the "
"attenuation profile, you can have almost any profile you desire."
msgstr ""
"显然你不仅限于简单的更改，例如反转衰减曲线，你几乎可以获得任何所需的曲线。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:225
msgid ""
"Here is another example of a different *Falloff Curve* profile graph, along "
"with its resultant render output:"
msgstr "下面是另一个 *Falloff Curve* 轮廓图的示例，以及它的结果的渲染输出："

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:233
msgid "Oscillating attenuation profile."
msgstr "振荡衰减曲线。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:238
msgid ""
"Render showing the effects of a \"wavelet\" profile graph on the light "
"attenuation."
msgstr "显示“波浪”轮廓图对光衰减的影响的渲染。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:242
msgid "Inverse Square"
msgstr "平方反比"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:247
msgid ""
"Render showing the Inverse Square lamp falloff type effect with default "
"settings."
msgstr "使用默认设置渲染显示反比平方灯光衰减类型效果。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:249
msgid ""
"This lamp falloff type attenuates its intensity according to inverse square "
"law, scaled by the *Distance* value. Inverse square is a sharper, realistic "
"decay, useful for lighting such as desk lamps and street lights. This is "
"similar to the old *Quad* option (and consequently, to the new *Lin/Quad "
"Weighted* option with *Linear* to 0.0 and *Quad* to 1.0), with slight changes."
msgstr ""
"这种灯的衰减类型根据平方反比定律减弱其强度，按其 *距离* 值缩放。平方反比是一种更"
"为锐利、逼真的衰减，可用于台灯和路灯等照明。这类似于旧的 *Quad* 选项（因此，新"
"的 *Lin/Quad Weighted*  选项的 *linear* 为0.0，*quad* 为1.0），但略有变化。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:258
msgid "Inverse Linear"
msgstr "线性反比"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:263
msgid ""
"Render showing the Inverse Linear lamp falloff type effect with default "
"settings."
msgstr "渲染显示具有默认设置的线性反比灯光衰减类型效果。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:265
msgid ""
"This lamp falloff type attenuates its intensity linearly, scaled by the "
"*Distance* value. This is the default setting, behaving the same as the default "
"in previous Blender versions without *Quad* switched on, and consequently, like "
"the new *Lin/Quad Weighted* option with *Linear* to 1.0 and *Quad* to 0.0. This "
"is not physically accurate, but can be easier to light with."
msgstr ""
"该灯光衰减类型线性衰减其强度，按 *Distance* 值缩放。这是默认设置，其行为与之前没"
"有打开 *Quad* 的Blender版本中的默认设置相同，因此，就像新的 *Lin/Quad "
"Weighted*  选项 *Linear*为1.0，*Quad* 为0.0一样。这在物理上不准确，但可以更容易"
"照明。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:274
msgid "Constant"
msgstr "常量/恒定"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:279
msgid ""
"Render showing the Constant lamp falloff type effect with default settings."
msgstr "使用默认设置渲染显示恒定灯衰减类型效果。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:281
msgid ""
"This lamp falloff type does not attenuate its intensity with distance. This is "
"useful for distant light sources like the sun or sky, which are so far away "
"that their falloff is not noticeable. *Sun* and *Hemi* lamps always have "
"constant falloff."
msgstr ""
"这种灯衰减类型强度不会随着距离而衰减。这对太阳或天空等遥远的光源很有用，因为它们"
"距离太远，以至于它们的衰减不明显。 *Sun* 和 *Hemi* 灯总是有不断的衰减。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:288
msgid "Inverse Coefficients"
msgstr "反比系数"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:290
msgid ""
"This lamp falloff type combines the *Inverse Square*, *Inverse Linear* and "
"*Constant* modes into a single inverse-quadratic formula:"
msgstr ""
"此灯光衰减类型将 *平方反比*、*线性反比* 和 *常量/恒定* 模式组合为一个二次反比公"
"式："

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:293
msgid ":math:`I = E × (1.0 / (Q × r^2 + L × r + C))`"
msgstr ":math:`I = E × (1.0 / (Q × r^2 + L × r + C))`"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:299
msgid "*C* is the current setting of the *Constant* slider setting."
msgstr "*C* 是 *Constant* 滑块的当前设置值。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:300
msgid "*L* is the current setting of the *Linear* slider setting."
msgstr "*L*  是当前的 *Linear* 滑块的值。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:301
msgid "*Q* is the current setting of the *Quadratic* slider setting."
msgstr "*Q* 是 *Quadratic* 滑块的当前设置值。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:304
msgid ""
"Such a falloff model is commonly used in real-time rendering applications via a "
"shading language like GLSL."
msgstr "这种衰减模型通常通过诸如GLSL的着色语言在实时渲染应用中使用。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:309
msgid "Sphere"
msgstr "球体"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:314
msgid ""
"Screenshot of the 3D View editor, showing the Sphere light clipping circle."
msgstr "3D视图编辑器的屏幕截图，显示了球体灯光剪裁圆圈。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:317
msgid ""
"The *Sphere* option restricts the light illumination range of a *Lamp* or "
"*Spot* lamp, so that it will completely stop illuminating an area once it "
"reaches the number of Blender Units away from the Lamp, as specified in the "
"*Distance* field."
msgstr ""
"*Sphere* 选项限制 *Lamp* 或 *Spot* 灯的光照范围，一旦达到远离灯光的Blender单元"
"数，它将完全停止照亮区域，如 *距离* 中所指定的区域。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:321
msgid ""
"When the *Sphere* option is active, a dotted sphere will appear around the "
"light source, indicating the demarcation point at which this light intensity "
"will be null."
msgstr ""
"当 *Sphere* 选项处于活动状态时，光源周围会出现一个虚线球体，表示此光强度为零的分"
"界点。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:325
msgid ""
"The *Sphere* option adds a term to the chosen attenuation law, whatever it is:"
msgstr "*sphere* 选项为所选的衰减定律添加的一个条件，无论它是什么："

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:327
msgid ":math:`I' = I × (D - r) / D` if :math:`r < D`;"
msgstr ":math:`I' = I × (D - r) / D` if :math:`r < D`;"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:329
msgid ":math:`I' = 0` otherwise;"
msgstr ":math:`I' = 0` 除此以外;"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:333
msgid ""
"*I'* is the required Intensity of light (with the *Sphere* option activated)."
msgstr "*I'* 是所需的光强度（激活了 *Sphere* 选项）。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:334
msgid ""
"*I* is the intensity of light calculated by the chosen attenuation law (without "
"the *Sphere* option)."
msgstr "*I* 是由所选衰减定律计算的光强度（不含 *球体* 选项）。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:338
msgid ""
"See the graphic at the end of the description of the *Lin/Quad Weighted* "
"attenuation option."
msgstr "请参阅 *Lin/Quad Weighted* 衰减选项说明末尾的图形。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:345
msgid ""
"Render showing the light attenuation of a Constant falloff light type with the "
"Sphere option active."
msgstr "渲染显示球体选项处于活动状态时恒定衰减光类型的光衰减。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:350
msgid ""
"Render showing the light attenuation of a Constant falloff light type with the "
"Sphere option deactivated."
msgstr "渲染显示恒定衰减光类型的光衰减，并禁用“球体”选项。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:354
msgid "Examples"
msgstr "例子"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:357
msgid "Distance Example"
msgstr "距离例子"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:359
msgid ""
"In this example, the *Lamp* has been set pretty close to the group of planes. "
"This causes the light to affect the front, middle and rear planes more "
"dramatically. Looking at the figure below, you can see that as the Distance is "
"increased, more and more objects become progressively brighter."
msgstr ""
"在此示例中，*Lamp* 已设置为非常接近于平面组。这会使光线更加剧烈地影响前，中，后"
"平面。查看下图，你可以看到随着距离的增加，越来越多的物体变得越来越亮。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:364
msgid "Various Distance settings (shadows disabled)."
msgstr "各种距离设置（禁用阴影）。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:368
msgid "Distance: 10."
msgstr "距离: 10。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:374
msgid "Distance: 100."
msgstr "距离: 100。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:380
msgid "Distance: 1000."
msgstr "距离: 1000。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:382
msgid ""
"The *Distance* parameter is controlling where the light is falling -- at a "
"linear rate by default -- to half its original value from the light's origin. "
"As you increase or decrease this value, you are changing where this half "
"falloff occurs. You could think of *Distance* as the surface of a sphere and "
"the surface is where the light's intensity has fallen to half its strength in "
"all directions. Note that the light's intensity continues to fall even after "
"*Distance*. *Distance* just specifies the distance where half of the light's "
"energy has weakened."
msgstr ""
"*Distance* 参数控制光线变弱的位置 - 默认为线性速率 - 为光源原点的原始值的一半。"
"当你增加或减少此值时，您正在改变发生这种半衰减的位置。你可以将*Distance* 视为球"
"体的表面，而表面是光线强度在所有方向上降至其强度的一半的地方。请注意，即使在 "
"*Distance* 之后，灯光的强度仍会继续下降。 *距离* 仅指定一半光能量减弱的距离。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:390
msgid ""
"Notice in Fig. :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-distance1000`, that the farthest "
"objects are very bright. This is because the falloff has been extended far into "
"the distance, which means the light is very strong when it hits the last few "
"objects. It is not until 1000 units that the light's intensity has fallen to "
"half of its original intensity."
msgstr ""
"请注意图  :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-distance1000` ，表示最远的物体是非常明"
"亮的。这是因为衰减已经延伸到远处，这意味着当它照射最后几个物体时光线非常强烈。直"
"到1000个单位，光的强度才下降到其原始强度的一半。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:395
msgid ""
"Contrast this with Fig. :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-distance100`, where the "
"falloff occurs so soon that the farther objects are barely lit. The light's "
"intensity has fallen by a half by time it even reaches the tenth object."
msgstr ""
"将其与图 :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-distance100` 进行对比，在这里衰减发生得"
"很快，更远的物体几乎不亮。光的强度在到达第十个物体时已经下降了一半。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:399
msgid ""
"You may be wondering why the first few planes appear to be dimmer? This is "
"because the surface angle between the light and the object's surface normal is "
"getting close to oblique. That is the nature of a *Lamp* light object. By "
"moving the light infinitely far away you would begin to approach the "
"characteristics of the *Sun* lamp type."
msgstr ""
"你可能想知道为什么前几个平面看起来更暗？这是因为光与物体表面法线之间的表面角度接"
"近倾斜。这就是 *Lamp* 灯光物体的本质。通过无限远地移动光线，你将开始接近 *Sun* "
"灯类型的特性。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:406
msgid "Inverse Square Example"
msgstr "平方反比例子"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:408
msgid ""
"*Inverse Square* makes the light's intensity falloff with a non-linear rate, or "
"specifically, a quadratic rate. The characteristic feature of using *Inverse "
"Square* is that the light's intensity begins to fall off very slowly but then "
"starts falling off very rapidly. We can see this in the Fig. :ref:`fig-bi-light-"
"attenuation-inverse-square` images."
msgstr ""
"*平方反比* 以非线性速率或特别的二次速率使光的强度衰减。使用 *平方反比* 的特征是"
"光的强度开始非常缓慢地下降但随后开始非常快速地下降。我们可以在图中看到这一点  :"
"ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-inverse-square` 。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:415
msgid "Inverse Square selected. (with the specified distances)."
msgstr "选中平方反比。 （具有指定的距离）。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:422
msgid "Inverse Square with 10."
msgstr "平方反比为10。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:428
msgid "Inverse Square with 100."
msgstr "平方反比为100。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:434
msgid "Inverse Square with 1000."
msgstr "平方反比为1000。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:436
msgid ""
"With *Inverse Square* selected, the *Distance* field specifies where the light "
"begins to fall off faster, roughly speaking; see the light attenuation "
"description in `Falloff types`_ for more info."
msgstr ""
"选择 *平方反比* 时，*距离* 字段指定光线开始快速下降的位置; 有关详细信息，请参阅 "
"`Falloff types`_ 中的光衰减描述。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:439
msgid ""
"In Fig. :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-inverse-square10`, the light's intensity "
"has fallen so quickly that the last few objects are not even lit."
msgstr ""
"在图 :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-inverse-square10` 中，灯的强度下降得太快，以"
"至于最后几个物体都没有被点亮。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:442
msgid ""
"Both Fig. :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-inverse-square100` and Fig. :ref:`fig-"
"bi-light-attenuation-inverse-square1000` appear to be almost identical and that "
"is because the *Distance* is set beyond the farthest object's distance which is "
"at about 40 BU out. Hence, all the objects get almost the full intensity of the "
"light."
msgstr ""
"图  :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-inverse-square100`  和图  :ref:`fig-bi-light-"
"attenuation-inverse-square1000`  看起来几乎相同，这是因为 *距离* 设置超出最远物"
"体的距离，大约40BU。因此，几乎所有物体都获得了光的全部强度。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:447
msgid ""
"As above, the first few objects are dimmer than farther objects because they "
"are very close to the light. Remember, the brightness of an object's surface is "
"also based on the angle between the surface normal of an object and the ray of "
"light coming from the lamp."
msgstr ""
"如上所述，前几个物体比较远的物体更暗，因为它们非常靠近光线。请记住，物体表面的亮"
"度也是基于物体表面法线与来自灯的光线之间的角度。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:451
msgid ""
"This means there are at least two things that are controlling the surface's "
"brightness: intensity and the angle between the light source and the surface's "
"normal."
msgstr ""
"这意味着至少有两件事情可以控制表面的亮度：强度和光源与表面法线之间的角度。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:456
msgid "Sphere Example"
msgstr "球体例子"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:462
msgid "Clipping Sphere."
msgstr "球体剪切。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:464
msgid ""
"*Sphere* indicates that the light's intensity is null at the *Distance* "
"distance and beyond, regardless of the chosen light's falloff. In Fig. :ref:"
"`fig-bi-light-attenuation-clip` you can see a side view example of the setup "
"with *Sphere* enabled and a distance of 10."
msgstr ""
"*sphere* 表示在 *距离* 及以上，灯光的强度为零，而与所选灯光的衰减无关。在图  :"
"ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-clip`  中，你可以看到启用了 *sphere* 且距离为10的"
"设置的侧视图示例。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:469
msgid "Any objects beyond the sphere receive no light from the lamp."
msgstr "球体之外的任何物体都不能从灯接收光。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:471
msgid ""
"The *Distance* field is now specifying both where the light's rays become null, "
"and the intensity's ratio falloff setting. Note that there is no abrupt "
"transition at the sphere: the light attenuation is progressive (for more "
"details, see the descriptions of the `Sphere`_ and `Falloff types`_ above)."
msgstr ""
"*Distance* 字段现在指定灯光光线变为零的位置和强度的比率衰减设置。请注意，球体上"
"没有突变：光衰减是渐进的（有关详细信息，请参见上面的  `Sphere`_  和 `Falloff "
"types`_  的描述）。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:477
msgid "Sphere enabled with the specified distances. Inverse Linear light falloff."
msgstr "使用指定距离启用球体。线性反比光衰减。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:484
msgid "Sphere with 10."
msgstr "球体为10。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:490
msgid "Sphere with 20."
msgstr "球体为20。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:496
msgid "Sphere with 40."
msgstr "球体为40。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:498
msgid ""
"In Fig. :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-sphere10`, the clipping sphere's radius "
"is 10 units, which means the light's intensity is also being controlled by 10 "
"units of distance. With a linear attenuation, the light's intensity has fallen "
"very low even before it gets to the first object."
msgstr ""
"在图  :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-sphere10 `中，裁剪球的半径为10个单位，这意"
"味着光的强度也由10个单位的距离控制。通过线性衰减，即使在到达第一个物体之前，光线"
"的强度也已经非常低。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:503
msgid ""
"In Fig. :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-sphere20`, the clipping sphere's radius "
"is now 20 BU and some light is reaching the middle objects."
msgstr ""
"在图 :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-sphere20` 中，裁剪球的半径现在是20单位，一些"
"光线到达中间的物体。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:506
msgid ""
"In Fig. :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-sphere40`, the clipping sphere's radius "
"is now 40 units, which is beyond the last object. However, the light does not "
"make it to the last few objects because the intensity has fallen to nearly 0."
msgstr ""
"在图 :ref:`fig-bi-light-attenuation-sphere40` 中，裁剪球的半径现在是40个单位，超"
"出了最后一个物体。然而，由于强度已降至接近0，因此光线不能进入最后几个物体。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lights/attenuation.rst:512
msgid ""
"If a *Lamp* light is set to not cast shadows, it illuminates through walls and "
"the like. If you want to achieve some nice effects like a fire, or a candle-lit "
"room interior seen from outside a window, the *Sphere* option is a must. By "
"carefully working on the *Distance* value you can make your warm fire lit shed "
"only within the room, while illuminating outside with a cool moonlight, the "
"latter achieved with a *Sun* or *Hemi* light or both."
msgstr ""
"如果 *Lamp* 灯设置为不投射阴影，则它会通过墙壁等照亮。如果你想要实现一些很好的效"
"果，如火，或从窗户外看到的烛光室内，*Sphere* 选项是必须的。通过仔细研究 "
"*Distance* 值，你可以让你的温暖的火焰只在房间内点亮，同时用凉爽的月光照亮外面，"
"后者用 *Sun* 或 *Hemi* 光或两者兼而有之。"
